  "body": "### Description\n\nSome production policies require that OIDC JWT tokens are introspected remotely only even if the OIDC provider can offer public verification keys. In such cases `quarkus-oidc` will only support the injection of `TokenIntrospection` representing a successful response from the OIDC provider and `JsonWebToken` injection will not work - however there is no reason to restrict it given that it has been confirmed to be valid by the OIDC provider itself and therefore  it should be possible to have both `TokenIntrospection` and `JsonWebToken` injected\n\n### Implementation ideas\n\n_No response_",
